tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (6.1%), indicating prediabetes. Glucose is currently normal. Renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile are unremarkable. Recommend monitoring glycemic control and considering lifestyle modifications to prevent progression to diabetes. No other laboratory abnormalities detected.
